As our first year of college comes to an end @grambling1901 had a ceremony to congratulate those who achieved an academic grade point average of 3.0 and higher and blessedly, My sister and I were two of the many students who qualified 👸🏾✨👸🏾! Congratulations to all & without God & being Motivated And Determined for greatness in all aspects, we wouldn’t be as far as we are today🥹… We ended last semester with Makyla(🩷) Majoring in Business Management with a Minor in Mass Communication with a 4.0 GPA and Makayla(💜) Majoring in Criminal Justice also having a Minor in Mass Communication with a 3.7 GPA. We are eternally grateful and blessed for the huge support system we’ve grown over the years, those who have donated to us & our parents towards our tuition funds & all of the love we have received 🥹… We will continue to make y’all proud and we ain’t leaving till we get what’s ours! THAT DIPLOMA 👩🏾‍🎓🩷💜
Big shout out to the mad dad🥹… He surprised us by flying down here all the way from California to watch us receive our medals🥲… We Love You Dad & thank you 🩷💜
